ecture\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                       PCAP Analyzer Service                                    в”Ӯ\nв”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\nв”Ӯ                                                                               в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ                         FastAPI Application                           в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ                                                                        в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   POST /analyze                                                        в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ pcap_file (UploadFile) OR pcap_path (Form)                      в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ SandboxRunner.upload_file() / upload_bytes()                    в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ _analyze_with_retries()                                         в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ _plan_script() вҶ’ PLANNER agent                              в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ _execute_once_in_runner() вҶ’ SandboxRunner.run()             в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ _repair_script() вҶ’ PLANNER agent (on failure)               в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ _report() вҶ’ REPORTER agent                                  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ AnalyzeResponse(script, results, report)                        в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ                                                                        в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                    в”Ӯ                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                    в–ј                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ LangChain/LangGraphв”Ӯ    в”Ӯ   CodeInterpreter в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ   OpenAI-compatibleв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   ReAct Agents     в”Ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв–¶в”Ӯ     Client        в”Ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв–¶в”Ӯ      LLM API       в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ  (PLANNER/REPORTER)в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ   (SandboxRunner) в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ  (Qwen/QwQ-32B)   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                                                               в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n### Data Flow\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ     в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ     в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ   Dify User     в”Ӯ     в”Ӯ  Dify Platform  в”Ӯ     в”Ӯ  Dify Plugin    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   Request       в”Ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–¶в”Ӯ   Workflow      в”Ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–¶в”Ӯ   Runtime       в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ     в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ     в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                                                        в”Ӯ\n                                                        в–ј\n                        в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n                        в”Ӯ  AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool._invoke()     в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ  Parameters:                                в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ  - router_url (required)                    в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ  - workload_manager_url (required)          в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ  - language (optional, default: python)     в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ  - code / command                           в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ  - session_id / session_reuse               в”Ӯ\n                        в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                                                        в”Ӯ\n                                                        в–ј\n                        в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n                        в”Ӯ  CodeInterpreterClient                      в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ  1. Create session (ControlPlaneClient)     в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ     POST /v1/code-interpreter               в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ  2. Init data plane (CodeInterpreterData...)в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ     base_url from router_url                в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ  3. Execute code/command                    в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ     POST api/execute                        в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ  4. Return JSON result                      в”Ӯ\n                        в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                                                        в”Ӯ\n                                                        в–ј\n                        в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n                        в”Ӯ  Router вҶ’ Sandbox Pod вҶ’ PicoD               в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ  JWT auth, session header routing           в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ  Local execution in workspace               в”Ӯ\n                        в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                                                        в”Ӯ\n                                                        в–ј\n                        в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n                        в”Ӯ  Tool.create_json_message(result)           в”Ӯ\n                        в”Ӯ  вҶ’ Dify workflow continues                  в”Ӯ\n                        в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Tool Parameter Types\n\n```python\nfrom typing import Optional, Dict, Any\nfrom enum import Enum\n\nclass LanguageType(str, Enum):\n    PYTHON = \"python\"\n    JAVASCRIPT = \"javascript\"\n    TYPESCRIPT = \"typescript\"\n\nclass ToolParameters:\n    router_url: str              # Required - AgentCube Router endpoint\n    workload_manager_url: str    # Required - Workload Manager endpoint\n    language: LanguageType       # Optional - default: python\n    code: Optional[str]          # Optional - code to execute\n    command: Optional[str]       # Optional - shell command to run\n    session_id: Optional[str]    # Optional - existing session to reuse\n    session_reuse: bool          # Optional - default: False\n    code_interpreter_id: Optional[str]  # Optional - interpreter name\n```\n\n### Execution Result Schema\n\n```python\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Any\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\n\nclass ExecutionResult(BaseModel):\n    stdout: str\n    stderr: str\n    exit_code: int\n    execution_time: float\n    files: Optional[List[Dict[str, Any]]] = None\n\nclass AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n    script: str\n    results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n    report: str\n```\n\n### Session State\n\n```python\nclass SessionState:\n    session_id: str\n    code_interpreter_name: str\n    namespace: str\n    created_at: float\n    ttl: int\n    last_activity: float\n    metadata: Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dify plugin вҖ” file map\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n| `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n| `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n| `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n| `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n| `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n\n## `manifest.yaml` structure (exact top-level keys)\n\nFrom source:\n\n- `version`: `0.0.2`\n- `type`: `plugin`\n- `author`: `volcano-sh`\n- `name`: `agentcube`\n- `label`: map `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` вҶ’ `Agentcube`\n- `description`: multilingual strings (AgentCube description)\n- `icon`: `icon.png`\n- `icon_dark`: `icon-dark.png`\n- `resource`: `memory`, `permission` subtree (`tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage` flags and sizes)\n- `plugins.tools`: list `[provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n- `meta`: `version`, `arch` (`amd64`, `arm64`), `runner` (`language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`), `minimum_dify_version: null`\n- `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, `verified`\n\n## `provider/agentcube.yaml` structure\n\n- `identity`: `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual), `description` (multilingual), `icon`\n- Commented `oauth_schema` block (not active)\n- `tools`: list `[tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml]`\n- `extra.python.source`: `provider/agentcube.py`\n\n## Tool definition (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`)\n\n- `identity.name`: `agentcube-code-interpreter`\n- `identity.author`: `agentcube`\n- `identity.label` / `description` (human + llm strings)\n- `parameters` (each has `name`, `type`, `required`, `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, `form`):\n\n| name | type | required | form | notes |\n|------|------|----------|------|-------|\n| `router_url` | string | true | form | |\n| `workload_manager_url` | string | true | form | |\n| `language` | select | false | llm | options: `python`, `javascript`, `typescript` |\n| `code` | string | false | llm | |\n| `command` | string | false | llm | |\n| `session_id` | string | false | llm | |\n| `session_reuse` | boolean | false | llm | |\n| `code_interpreter_id` | string | false | llm | |\n\n- `extra.python.source`: `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n\n## Provider implementation (`provider/agentcube.py`)\n\n```python\nfrom dify_plugin import ToolProvider\nfrom dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\n\nclass AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider):\n    def _validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n        try:\n            \"\"\" IMPLEMENT YOUR VALIDATION HERE \"\"\"\n        except Exception as e:\n            raise ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))\n```\n\n(OAuth helper methods are present only as comments.)\n\n## Tool implementation (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`)\n\n```python\nfrom collections.abc import Generator\nfrom typing import Any\nfrom dify_plugin import Tool\nfrom dify_plugin.entities.tool import ToolInvokeMessage\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\nclass AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n    def _invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]:\n        result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n        yield self.create_json_message(result)\n\n    def execute(\n        self,\n        router_url=None,\n        workload_manager_url=None,\n        language=\"python\",\n        code_interpreter_id=None,\n        session_id=None,\n        code=None,\n        command=None,\n        session_reuse=False,\n        **kwargs\n    ): ...\n```\n\n## Plugin dependencies (`integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`)\n\n```\ndify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\nagentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n```\n\n## PCAP analyzer вҖ” application structure (`example/pcap-analyzer/`)\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI app, agents, sandbox runner, analysis orchestration, `uvicorn` entry |\n| `requirements.txt` | FastAPI, uvicorn, LangChain / LangGraph stack, multipart, etc. |\n| `Dockerfile` | `uv` base image, installs reqs, copies `sdk-python/agentcube` + `pcap_analyzer.py` |\n| `deployment.yaml` | K8s Deployment + env for OpenAI-compatible API and AgentCube URLs |\n| `README.md` | Documentation |\n\n## FastAPI application (`pcap_analyzer.py`)\n\n### Globals / config (selected)\n\n| Name | Source | Default / value |\n|------|--------|-----------------|\n| `API_KEY` | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | required at startup |\n| `API_BASE_URL` | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` |\n| `MODEL_NAME` | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` |\n| `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | env | `my-interpreter` |\n| `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | env | `default` |\n| `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | env | `5` |\n| `SERVER_HOST` | constant | `0.0.0.0` |\n| `SERVER_PORT` | constant | `8000` |\n| `SERVER_RELOAD` | constant | `True` |\n\n### Core classes / functions\n\n```python\nclass SandboxRunner:\n    def __init__(self, name: str = \"my-interpreter\", namespace: str = \"default\", warmup_sec: int = 5): ...\n    def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n    def upload_bytes(self, data: bytes, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n    def run(self, command: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def stop(self): ...\n\ndef build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt: str): ...\ndef invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text: str) -> str: ...\ndef build_planner_agent(llm): ...\ndef build_reporter_agent(llm): ...\n\ndef _plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path: str) -> str: ...\ndef _repair_script(agent, prev_script: str, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\ndef _execute_once_in_runner(runner: SandboxRunner, pcap_local_path: str, script: str) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\ndef _analyze_with_retries(..., max_retries: int = 2) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\ndef _report(agent, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n\nclass AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n    script: str\n    results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n    report: str\n\napp = FastAPI(title=\"PCAP Analyzer вҖ” Env-Only Config\")\n```\n\n### FastAPI endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Signature / behavior |\n|--------|------|----------------------|\n| (event) | startup | `on_startup()` вҶ’ builds `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, `REPORTER`; fails if no API key |\n| `POST` | `/analyze` | `async def analyze_endpoint(pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None), pcap_path: str = Form(None))` вҶ’ `response_model=AnalyzeResponse` |\n\n### Imports of note\n\n```python\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File, Form, HTTPException\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\nimport uvicorn\nfrom langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\nfrom langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\nfrom langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, AIMessage\nfrom agentcube.code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n```\n\n## Kubernetes deployment (`deployment.yaml`)\n\n- `Deployment` `pcap-analyzer` in `namespace: default`\n- Container `pcap-analyzer`, image `pcap-analyzer:latest`, `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n- Container port `8000` TCP\n- Resources: requests `cpu: 200m`, `memory: 100Mi`; limits `cpu: 1`, `memory: 1Gi`\n- Env: `OPENAI_API_KEY` from secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`; `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n- Command: `[\"uv\"]`, args: `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n\n## Dockerfile highlights\n\n- Base: `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`\n- `uv venv` + `uv pip install -r requirements.txt`\n- Copies `sdk-python/agentcube` вҶ’ `./agentcube/`, `pcap_analyzer.py` вҶ’ `./`\n- `ENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, exposes `8000`\n- `CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n\n## PCAP example Python dependencies (`example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`)\n\nPinned packages include: `fastapi==0.120.0`, `uvicorn==0.38.0`, `langchain==1.0.2`, `langchain-classic==1.0.0`, `langchain-community==0.4.1`, `langchain-core==1.0.1`, `langchain-openai==1.0.1`, `langchain-text-splitters==1.0.0`, `langgraph==1.0.1`, `langgraph-checkpoint==3.0.0`, `langgraph-prebuilt==1.0.1`, `langgraph-sdk==0.2.9`, `langsmith==0.4.38`, `paramiko==4.0.0`, `python-multipart==0.0.20`\n\n*(The Dockerfile vendors `agentcube` from the monorepo copy; it is not listed in this `requirements.txt`.)*\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories\n\n| Category | Description | Recovery Action |\n|----------|-------------|-----------------|\n| `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` | Invalid credentials provided | Raise with descriptive message |\n| `CommandExecutionError` | Remote command failed (non-zero exit) | Include exit_code, stderr in result |\n| `SessionError` | Session creation/deletion failed | Log warning, return error JSON |\n| `DataPlaneError` | Router/sandbox communication failed | Retry with exponential backoff |\n| `ValueError` | Missing required parameters (router_url) | Raise before execution attempt |\n\n### Plugin Error Handling Pattern\n\n```python\nfrom dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError, SessionError\n\nclass AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n    def _invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]:\n        try:\n            if not tool_parameters.get(\"router_url\"):\n                yield self.create_json_message({\n                    \"error\": \"router_url is required\",\n                    \"error_type\": \"ValidationError\"\n                })\n                return\n            \n            result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n            yield self.create_json_message(result)\n        except CommandExecutionError as e:\n            yield self.create_json_message({\n                \"error\": str(e),\n                \"error_type\": \"CommandExecutionError\",\n                \"exit_code\": e.exit_code,\n                \"stderr\": e.stderr\n            })\n        except SessionError as e:\n            yield self.create_json_message({\n                \"error\": str(e),\n                \"error_type\": \"SessionError\"\n            })\n        except Exception as e:\n            yield self.create_json_message({\n                \"error\": str(e),\n                \"error_type\": \"UnexpectedError\"\n            })\n```\n\n### PCAP Analyzer Error Handling\n\n```python\nfrom fastapi import HTTPException\n\n@app.on_event(\"startup\")\nasync def on_startup():\n    if not API_KEY:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"OPENAI_API_KEY is required at startup\")\n\n@app.post(\"/analyze\", response_model=AnalyzeResponse)\nasync def analyze_endpoint(\n    pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None),\n    pcap_path: str = Form(None)\n):\n    if not pcap_file and not pcap_path:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=400, detail=\"Either pcap_file or pcap_path required\")\n    \n    try:\n        runner = SandboxRunner(\n            name=CODEINTERPRETER_NAME,\n            namespace=SANDBOX_NAMESPACE,\n            warmup_sec=int(SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC)\n        )\n        result = _analyze_with_retries(runner, pcap_file or pcap_path)\n        return result\n    except CommandExecutionError as e:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=f\"Sandbox error: {e.stderr}\")\n    finally:\n        runner.stop()\n```\n\n### Error Response Schema\n\n```python\nclass ErrorResponse(BaseModel):\n    error: str\n    error_type: str\n    exit_code: Optional[int] = None\n    stderr: Optional[str] = None\n    retry_count: Optional[int] = None\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Tool Provider Tests\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import Mock, patch\nfrom dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\n\ndef test_provider_validate_credentials_success():\n    provider = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider()\n    credentials = {\"router_url\": \"http://router:8080\", \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://wm:8080\"}\n    provider._validate_credentials(credentials)\n    # Should not raise\n\ndef test_provider_validate_credentials_missing_url():\n    provider = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider()\n    credentials = {\"router_url\": \"\", \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://wm:8080\"}\n    with pytest.raises(ToolProviderCredentialValidationError):\n        provider._validate_credentials(credentials)\n```\n\n#### Tool Invocation Tests\n\n```python\ndef test_tool_invoke_missing_router_url():\n    tool = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool()\n    messages = list(tool._invoke({\"workload_manager_url\": \"http://wm:8080\"}))\n    result = json.loads(messages[0].message)\n    assert result[\"error_type\"] == \"ValidationError\"\n    assert \"router_url\" in result[\"error\"]\n\ndef test_tool_invoke_code_execution():\n    tool = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool()\n    with patch.object(tool, 'execute') as mock_execute:\n        mock_execute.return_value = {\"stdout\": \"hello\", \"stderr\": \"\", \"exit_code\": 0}\n        messages = list(tool._invoke({\n            \"router_url\": \"http://router:8080\",\n            \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://wm:8080\",\n            \"code\": \"print('hello')\"\n        }))\n        result = json.loads(messages[0].message)\n        assert result[\"exit_code\"] == 0\n        assert result[\"stdout\"] == \"hello\"\n\ndef test_tool_invoke_command_failure():\n    tool = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool()\n    with patch.object(tool, 'execute') as mock_execute:\n        mock_execute.side_effect = CommandExecutionError(\n            exit_code=1, stderr=\"error output\", command=\"ls /nonexistent\"\n        )\n        messages = list(tool._invoke({\n            \"router_url\": \"http://router:8080\",\n            \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://wm:8080\",\n            \"command\": \"ls /nonexistent\"\n        }))\n        result = json.loads(messages[0].message)\n        assert result[\"error_type\"] == \"CommandExecutionError\"\n        assert result[\"exit_code\"] == 1\n```\n\n#### Session Reuse Tests\n\n```python\ndef test_tool_session_reuse():\n    tool = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool()\n    with patch('agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient') as mock_client:\n        mock_client.return_value.session_id = \"existing-session-123\"\n        mock_client.return_value.execute_command.return_value = \"output\"\n        \n        messages = list(tool._invoke({\n            \"router_url\": \"http://router:8080\",\n            \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://wm:8080\",\n            \"session_id\": \"existing-session-123\",\n            \"session_reuse\": True,\n            \"command\": \"echo test\"\n        }))\n        # Verify client was initialized with existing session_id\n        mock_client.assert_called_with(session_id=\"existing-session-123\")\n```\n\n#### PCAP Analyzer Tests\n\n```python\ndef test_analyze_endpoint_missing_input():\n    client = TestClient(app)\n    response = client.post(\"/analyze\")\n    assert response.status_code == 400\n\ndef test_analyze_endpoint_with_file():\n    client = TestClient(app)\n    pcap_content = b\"mock pcap data\"\n    with patch('pcap_analyzer._analyze_with_retries') as mock_analyze:\n        mock_analyze.return_value = {\n            \"script\": \"# analysis script\",\n            \"results\": [{\"stdout\": \"ok\"}],\n            \"report\": \"Analysis complete\"\n        }\n        response = client.post(\n            \"/analyze\",\n            files={\"pcap_file\": (\"test.pcap\", pcap_content)}\n        )\n        assert response.status_code == 200\n        assert response.json()[\"report\"] == \"Analysis complete\"\n\ndef test_startup_without_api_key():\n    with patch.dict(os.environ, {\"OPENAI_API_KEY\": \"\"}):\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            on_startup()\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### End-to-End Plugin Test\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_plugin_e2e_code_execution():\n    \"\"\"Test full plugin invocation with live AgentCube backend.\"\"\"\n    tool = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool()\n    messages = list(tool._invoke({\n        \"router_url\": os.environ[\"ROUTER_URL\"],\n        \"workload_manager_url\": os.environ[\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"],\n        \"language\": \"python\",\n        \"code\": \"import sys; print(sys.version)\"\n    }))\n    result = json.loads(messages[0].message)\n    assert result[\"exit_code\"] == 0\n    assert \"3.12\" in result[\"stdout\"]  # Python version check\n```\n\n#### PCAP Analyzer E2E Test\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_pcap_analyzer_e2e():\n    \"\"\"Test PCAP analyzer with real sandbox.\"\"\"\n    client = TestClient(app)\n    pcap_path = \"tests/fixtures/sample.pcap\"\n    \n    response = client.post(\n        \"/analyze\",\n        data={\"pcap_path\": pcap_path}\n    )\n    assert response.status_code == 200\n    data = response.json()\n    assert \"script\" in data\n    assert \"results\" in data\n    assert \"report\" in data\n```\n\n### Test Configuration\n\n```python\n# tests/conftest.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_code_interpreter_client():\n    with patch('agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient') as mock:\n        client = mock.return_value\n        client.execute_command.return_value = \"mock output\"\n        client.run_code.return_value = \"mock output\"\n        client.session_id = \"test-session-123\"\n        yield client\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_sandbox_runner():\n    with patch('pcap_analyzer.SandboxRunner') as mock:\n        runner = mock.return_value\n        runner.run.return_value = {\"stdout\": \"ok\", \"stderr\": \"\", \"exit_code\": 0}\n        runner.upload_file.return_value = True\n        yield runner\n```\n\n---\n\n## Metrics\n\n### Prometheus Metrics\n\n```python\nfrom prometheus_client import Counter, Histogram, Gauge\n\nTOOL_INVOCATIONS = Counter(\n    'agentcube_dify_tool_invocations_total',\n    'Total tool invocations',\n    ['tool_name', 'language', 'status']\n)\n\nEXECUTION_DURATION = Histogram(\n    'agentcube_dify_execution_duration_seconds',\n    'Code execution duration',\n    ['language'],\n    buckets=[0.1, 0.5, 1, 5, 10, 30, 60, 120]\n)\n\nSESSION_CREATIONS = Counter(\n    'agentcube_dify_session_creations_total',\n    'Session creation count',\n    ['session_type']  # 'new' or 'reuse'\n)\n\nACTIVE_SESSIONS = Gauge(\n    'agentcube_dify_active_sessions',\n    'Currently active sessions'\n)\n\nPCAP_ANALYSIS_DURATION = Histogram(\n    'agentcube_pcap_analysis_duration_seconds',\n    'PCAP analysis total duration',\n    buckets=[1, 5, 10, 30, 60, 120, 300]\n)\n```\n\n### Metric Usage in Tool\n\n```python\nclass AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n    def _invoke(self, tool_parameters):\n        start_time = time.time()\n        language = tool_parameters.get(\"language\", \"python\")\n        session_type = \"reuse\" if tool_parameters.get(\"session_reuse\") else \"new\"\n        \n        try:\n            result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n            status = \"success\" if result.get(\"exit_code\") == 0 else \"error\"\n            \n            TOOL_INVOCATIONS.labels(\n                tool_name=\"agentcube-code-interpreter\",\n                language=language,\n                status=status\n            ).inc()\n            \n            EXECUTION_DURATION.labels(language=language).observe(\n                time.time() - start_time\n            )\n            \n            SESSION_CREATIONS.labels(session_type=session_type).inc()\n            \n            yield self.create_json_message(result)\n        except Exception as e:\n            TOOL_INVOCATIONS.labels(\n                tool_name=\"agentcube-code-interpreter\",\n                language=language,\n                status=\"exception\"\n            ).inc()\n            yield self.create_json_message({\"error\": str(e)})\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Plugin | PCAP Analyzer | Default |\n|----------|--------|---------------|---------|\n| `ROUTER_URL` | Required | Required | - |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Required | Required | - |\n| `MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT` | Plugin entry | - | `120` |\n| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | - | Required | - |\n| `OPENAI_API_BASE` | - | Optional | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` |\n| `OPENAI_MODEL` | - | Optional | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` |\n| `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | - | Optional | `my-interpreter` |\n| `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | - | Optional | `default` |\n| `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | - | Optional | `5` |\n\n### Kubernetes Configuration\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Secret\nmetadata:\n  name: pcap-analyzer-secrets\ntype: Opaque\ndata:\n  openai-api-key: <base64-encoded-key>\n---\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: pcap-analyzer\nspec:\n  template:\n    spec:\n      containers:\n      - name: pcap-analyzer\n        image: pcap-analyzer:latest\n        env:\n        - name: OPENAI_API_KEY\n          valueFrom:\n            secretKeyRef:\n              name: pcap-analyzer-secrets\n              key: openai-api-key\n        - name: ROUTER_URL\n          value: \"http://agentcube-router:8080\"\n        - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n          value: \"http://workload-manager:8080\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Build Configuration\n\n### Plugin Package Build\n\n```bash\n# Create plugin package\ncd integrations/dify-plugin\npip install dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\ndify-plugin package .\n# Output: agentcube.difypkg\n```\n\n### Docker Build (PCAP Analyzer)\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Install dependencies\nRUN uv venv && uv pip install -r requirements.txt\n\n# Vendor SDK from monorepo\nCOPY sdk-python/agentcube ./agentcube/\nCOPY example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py ./\n\nENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"\nEXPOSE 8000\n\nCMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]\n```\n\n### Makefile Targets\n\n```makefile\n.PHONY: build-plugin build-pcap-analyzer package-plugin\n\nbuild-plugin:\n\tcd integrations/dify-plugin && pip install -r requirements.txt\n\nbuild-pcap-analyzer:\n\tdocker build -t pcap-analyzer:latest -f integrations/example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile .\n\npackage-plugin:\n\tcd integrations/dify-plugin && dify-plugin package .\n\ntest-integrations:\n\tpytest integrations/tests/ -v\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n### Dify Plugin\n\n- [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py` - Plugin entry point\n- [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml` - Root manifest\n- [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml` - Provider descriptor\n- [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py` - Provider implementation\n- [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` - Tool schema\n- [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` - Tool implementation\n- [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt` - Dependencies\n- [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/GUIDE.md` - User guide\n- [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/README.md` - Documentation\n- [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/PRIVACY.md` - Privacy policy\n- [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/.difyignore` - Package ignore rules\n- [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/icon.png` - Light theme icon\n- [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/icon-dark.png` - Dark theme icon\n\n### PCAP Analyzer Example\n\n- [ ] `integrations/example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` - FastAPI app\n- [ ] `integrations/example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` - Dependencies\n- [ ] `integrations/example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` - Container build\n- [ ] `integrations/example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` - Kubernetes manifest\n- [ ] `integrations/example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` - Documentation\n\n### Testing\n\n- [ ] Unit tests for provider credential validation\n- [ ] Unit tests for tool invocation\n- [ ] Unit tests for session reuse logic\n- [ ] Unit tests for PCAP analyzer endpoints\n- [ ] Integration tests with mock backend\n- [ ] E2E tests with live AgentCube backend\n\n### CI/CD\n\n- [ ] GitHub workflow for plugin packaging\n- [ ] GitHub workflow for PCAP analyzer Docker build\n- [ ] GitHub workflow for integration tests\n- [ ] Dify marketplace publishing automation\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Dify Plugin Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `dify-plugin` | `>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` | Dify plugin framework |\n| `agentcube-sdk` | `>=0.0.10` | AgentCube Python client |\n| `requests` | (via agentcube-sdk) | HTTP client |\n| `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` (via agentcube-sdk) | JWT handling |\n| `cryptography` | (via agentcube-sdk) | Crypto utilities |\n\n### PCAP Analyzer Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `fastapi` | `==0.120.0` | Web framework |\n| `uvicorn` | `==0.38.0` | ASGI server |\n| `langchain` | `==1.0.2` | LLM framework |\n| `langchain-openai` | `==1.0.1` | OpenAI integration |\n| `langgraph` | `==1.0.1` | Agent orchestration |\n| `langgraph-prebuilt` | `==1.0.1` | Prebuilt agent patterns |\n| `python-multipart` | `==0.0.20` | File upload handling |\n| `paramiko` | `==4.0.0` | SSH client |\n| `agentcube` | (vendored) | AgentCube SDK |\n\n### External Service Dependencies\n\n| Service | Purpose | Protocol |\n|---------|---------|----------|\n| AgentCube Router | Session routing | HTTP |\n| Workload Manager | Session CRUD | HTTP |\n| Sandbox Pod (PicoD) | Code execution | HTTP |\n| OpenAI-compatible API | LLM inference | HTTP |\n| Kubernetes | Container orchestration | API |\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts Summary\n\n### Dify Plugin API\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| (internal) | `_validate_credentials` | Provider credential check |\n| (internal) | `_invoke` | Tool execution entry |\n| Router `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{name}/invocations/api/execute` | POST | Code/command execution |\n| Router `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{name}/invocations/api/files` | POST/GET | File operations |\n| Workload Manager `/v1/code-interpreter` | POST | Session creation |\n| Workload Manager `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}` | DELETE | Session deletion |\n\n### PCAP Analyzer API\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Request | Response |\n|----------|--------|---------|----------|\n| `/analyze` | POST | `pcap_file: UploadFile` or `pcap_path: str` | `AnalyzeResponse` |\n| `/health` | GET | - | `{status: \"ok\"}` |\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Plugin Security\n\n- Credentials validated before execution\n- Session IDs used for request routing\n- JWT tokens handled by Router (not SDK)\n- No secrets in plugin package\n\n### PCAP Analyzer Security\n\n- API key required at startup (fail-fast)\n- Secrets mounted from Kubernetes Secret\n- Sandbox isolation via AgentCube\n- No direct filesystem access\n\n### Kubernetes RBAC\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: pcap-analyzer\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"create\", \"delete\"]\n```\n","additions":587,"deletions":0},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/integrations/design.md","time":{"start":1775892320858,"end":1775892320888}}}}
